OU TUTOR DATA PROTECTION GUIDE
==============================

FOR BRAILLE DISPLAY OR EMBOSSER
GRADE 2 ENGLISH BRAILLE

------------------------------------
IMPORTANT NOTICE
------------------------------------

You should NOT keep student work or
personal data for more than ONE YEAR
after the student leaves your tuition.

This is Open University policy and
UK GDPR law.

------------------------------------
SECTION 1: WHAT TO DELETE
------------------------------------

Student Work:
- TMA submissions
- Marked copies of assignments
- PT3 feedback forms
- Annotated documents
- Draft feedback

Personal Information:
- Student names
- PI numbers
- Email addresses
- Postal addresses
- Phone numbers

Communication Records:
- Emails to and from students
- Tutorial notes with names
- Assignment queries

------------------------------------
SECTION 2: WHEN TO DELETE
------------------------------------

When student completes module:
  Keep for maximum 1 year then delete

When student withdraws:
  Delete within 1 year of withdrawal

When student transfers to another tutor:
  Delete immediately after handover

For complaints or appeals:
  Keep until resolved then delete
  within 1 year

At end of each academic year:
  Review all stored data

------------------------------------
SECTION 3: HOW TO DELETE
------------------------------------

Using the eTMA Handler:

Step 1: Run the etmaHandler script

Step 2: Choose option 5 for data
        protection sanitise

Step 3: Follow the prompts to:
  - Preview what will be deleted
  - Delete specific courses
  - Delete all student data
  - Delete the returns folder

------------------------------------
SECTION 4: SAFE DELETION STEPS
------------------------------------

Step 1: Verify all marked work has
        been uploaded to the OU

Step 2: Run the sanitisation tool
        in preview mode first

Step 3: Confirm files are no longer
        needed

Step 4: Delete by course or all at once

------------------------------------
SECTION 5: WHAT YOU MAY KEEP
------------------------------------

You may keep:
- Your teaching notes without student
  names or identifiers
- Generic feedback templates
- Module materials not student specific
- Anonymised statistical records

------------------------------------
SECTION 6: WHAT YOU MUST NOT KEEP
------------------------------------

You must not keep:
- Named grade lists
- Individual student records
- Personal correspondence with students
- Identifiable performance data

------------------------------------
SECTION 7: DATA BREACH REPORTING
------------------------------------

If you discover a data breach:

Step 1: Report immediately to the OU
        Data Protection team

Step 2: Note what data was affected

Step 3: Identify how breach occurred

Step 4: Follow OU instructions

Contact: dataprotection at open.ac.uk

------------------------------------
SECTION 8: GOLDEN RULES
------------------------------------

Rule 1: If you have not used a student
file in the past year and the module
has finished, delete it.

Rule 2: When in doubt, delete. You can
request data from the OU if needed.

Rule 3: It is easier to explain why you
deleted data than why you kept it.

